conclusion: Analyze the flow of liquid through the system of baffles and containers to determine which container (E or F) the liquid will flow into.
The arrows labeled A, B, C, and D indicate the direction of flow.
From A, the liquid flows to E.
From B, the liquid flows to F.
From C, the liquid flows to F.
From D, the liquid flows to E.
Since the arrows point from A to E and from B to F, the liquid will flow from A to E and then from E to F.
The liquid will flow into container F after passing through the baffles.
